What you need to know:  Kenya is considering debt-for-nature or climate swaps to unlock funds for the construction of water dams amid a cash crunch that has risks derailing spending on key development projects.Debt-for-nature or climate swaps are financial deals that typically allow a country to restructure its debt at a lower interest rate or longer maturity, with the proceeds being allocated to conservation or green projects.This innovative financing model has gained traction among developing countries and has been successfully deployed in Seychelles, Belize, and Barbados.